# .ctxignore — paths that stay REAL files on disk (ctx never proxies them).
#
# The only reason to keep a .md on disk is a file-native consumer: a docs build,
# repo tooling that reads markdown, or a human who insists on their editor.
# Everything else lives only in ctx (frontend for humans, ctx_read for agents).
#
# One glob per line; matched against both repo-relative and absolute paths.

# Repo conventions that must remain on-disk files
README.md
CHANGELOG.md
LICENSE.md
REFONTE.md

# Agent harness files the tooling reads directly
**/CLAUDE.md
**/AGENTS.md

# Anything a build/site generator consumes
docs/site/**
